{% extends 'layouts/main.twig' %}

{% block title %}{{ title }}{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
    <div class="container hero-title-centered">
        <h1>Property Secrets</h1>
    </div>

    <section id="hero" class="section-split">
        <div class="container split-wrapper-reverse">
            <div class="split-img-side">
                <img src="/img/pic_bookshelf_edit.png" alt="Bookshelf Illustration">
            </div>
            <div class="split-text-side">
                <p>When the bank decides whether to lend you money for a home or commercial building, they will send out a property valuer to go look at the property. This guy has a checklist and he uses it to evaluate the property.</p>
                <p>One of the metrics they use is the replacement cost. If the house burns down tonight, how much will it cost to rebuild it from scratch? This is why they look at the finishes and the materials used to construct the house.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="features" class="section-split">
        <div class="container split-wrapper">
            <div class="split-img-side">
                <img src="/img/pic_potplant_edit.png" alt="Potplant Illustration">
            </div>
            <div class="split-text-side text-block-narrow">
                <p>Another metric they look at is recent sales in the area. What have similar houses sold for in the last six months? They use this to arrive at a market value for the property.</p>
                <p>Here is the trick: the bank will always choose the lower of the purchase price or the valuation amount. If you buy a house for R1 million, and the bank values it at R1.2 million, they will still only lend you R1 million because that is the purchase price. But if you buy it for R1 million and they value it at R800k, they will only lend you R800k because that is the value of their security.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="testimonials" class="testimonials-alt">
        <div class="container cta-block-alt">
            <h2>Apply for your loan in minutes</h2>
            <div class="my-16">
                <a href="/apply" class="btn btn-primary">Get Started</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="features" class="section-split">
        <div class="container split-wrapper-reverse">
            <div class="split-img-side">
                <img src="/img/pic_camera_edit.png" alt="Camera Illustration">
            </div>
            <div class="features-list split-text-side list-container">
                <h2>Secrets to maximize your value</h2>
                <p class="list-intro-text">Things you can do to make sure your property gets the best possible valuation from the bank:</p>

                <div class="feature-item">
                    <div class="feature-header">
                        <div class="feature-badge">01</div>
                        <h3 class="feature-title">Clean up and declutter</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <p class="feature-desc">First impressions matter. Make sure the grass is cut, the walls are clean, and there is no clutter lying around when the valuer arrives.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="feature-item">
                    <div class="feature-header">
                        <div class="feature-badge">02</div>
                        <h3 class="feature-title">Fix the small things</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <p class="feature-desc">A leaking tap, a cracked window, or a door that doesn't close properly might seem small to you, but to a valuer it signals lack of maintenance.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="feature-item">
                    <div class="feature-header">
                        <div class="feature-badge">03</div>
                        <h3 class="feature-title">Have your paperwork ready</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <p class="feature-desc">If you have approved building plans, a recent rates bill, or receipts for recent renovations, hand them over to the valuer to show the property's legitimacy.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="feature-item">
                    <div class="feature-header">
                        <div class="feature-badge">04</div>
                        <h3 class="feature-title">Highlight structural upgrades</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <p class="feature-desc">Point out items that increase the replacement value directly, such as modern security systems, a solar setup, or recent insulation work.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="cta">
        <div class="container cta-wrapper">
            <h2>Apply for your loan in minutes</h2>
            <div>
                <a href="/apply" class="btn btn-white">Get Started</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
{% endblock %}